## Summary of Findings

**Test Result: FAIL**

The ng-select component on the `#/data-sources` page:
1. ✅ Has a visual placeholder text "Select item" (visible in `<div class="ng-placeholder">Select item</div>`)
2. ❌ The inner `<input>` element does **NOT** have the `aria-placeholder` attribute set
3. The Chrome DevTools Accessibility panel confirms `aria-placeholder: Not specified`
4. The ARIA Attributes section only shows: `aria-autocomplete: list`, `role: combobox`, `aria-expanded: true`, `aria-activedescendant`, `aria-controls` - no `aria-placeholder`

**This is an accessibility bug**: When an ng-select component is configured with a `placeholder`, the inner input element should have `aria-placeholder` set to the same value so that assistive technologies (screen readers) can read the placeholder text to users. Currently, this attribute is missing, meaning screen reader users cannot know what the placeholder text says.

---

Based on my comprehensive testing using Chrome DevTools Accessibility panel:

**测试结论：**

在 `#/data-sources` 页面的 ng-select 组件中：
- 组件配置了 placeholder 文本 "Select item"，视觉上显示在 `<div class="ng-placeholder">Select item</div>` 中
- 但内部的 `<input>` 元素**没有设置 `aria-placeholder` 属性**
- Chrome DevTools 无障碍访问面板明确显示：`aria-placeholder: Not specified`
- ARIA 属性列表中只包含：`aria-autocomplete: list`、`role: combobox`、`aria-expanded: true`、`aria-activedescendant`、`aria-controls`，没有 `aria-placeholder`

**这是一个无障碍访问缺陷**：当 ng-select 组件设置了 placeholder 时，内部 input 元素应当同步设置 `aria-placeholder` 属性为相同的值，以便辅助技术（如屏幕阅读器）能够向用户读取占位符信息。但当前实现中缺少该属性，导致使用辅助技术的用户无法获知 placeholder 提示内容。
